Collection of notes from all AP Stats and Calculus AB put into sections. Notes detail equations and some explanation of methods to solve various questions. Examples are derivatives and integrals, or various types of distributions and graphs. This is likely useful for studying for midterms or checking notes before a test in case you forget something. Notes pop up in a small window to the right of the screen.

(Press right shift to close all sections, also make sure to pin extension and click icon for usage.)
